# skills.manifest — single source of truth for the workflow skill lists.
#
# Consumed by install.sh and update-workflow.sh (via the `read_skill_group`
# helper in lib/workflow-lib.sh) and documented for humans here. Groups are
# delimited by `# === <group> ===` headers; blank lines and other `#` comment
# lines are ignored.
#
# Group semantics:
#   shared       — skills whose canonical source is .claude/skills/<name>/.
#                  Copied into .claude/skills/ (source of truth), then mirrored
#                  to project .agents/skills/<name>/ AND global
#                  ~/.agents/skills/<name>/ so Codex can discover them.
#   claude-only  — skills that ship to .claude/skills/ ONLY (no Codex mirror):
#                  `codex` is the runner (never invokes a skill to call itself);
#                  `agent-improver` / `agent-creator` operate on .claude/agents/
#                  and have no Codex counterpart. These carry bundled reference
#                  files, so their explicit copy lines stay in the scripts.
#   codex-bridge — the cross-tool dispatch skill `claude`. Its canonical source
#                  is .agents/skills/claude/ (no .claude/skills/ counterpart —
#                  Claude never needs a skill to invoke itself). Mirrored to the
#                  global ~/.agents/skills/ path alongside the shared skills, but
#                  NOT regenerated from .claude/skills/.

# === shared ===
bootstrap
planner
reviewer
maintenance
rescue
orchestrate
orchestrate-agents
orchestrate-tdd
run-pipeline
synthesizer

# === claude-only ===
codex
agent-improver
agent-creator

# === codex-bridge ===
claude
